caption: Average korean fusion food. I got to try their kimchi fried rice balls and the kimchi fried rice with chicken. Rice balls were good but the rice inside was a bit too bland for my taste. The chicken in the fried rice was also a little dry, but other than that, they were okay overall.
I am a big fan of their fried tofu and their bowls. A great cure for the munchies!

Some of the best food out there. It was my SO's first time there and she loved the kimchi fried rice bowl. I went with my go to Olitoki Burrito with beef. It was my first in store visit and the staff was incredibly nice. Will definitely be back!
Pretty good! I got a rice bowl with spicy pork and really enjoyed it.
Fine place for tasty Asian food. I was so stuffed.
Delicious food and very fast service. The delivery girl was very polite and friendly. I will definitely order from here again.

We love to go out. Last night we  visited this delicious place which we didn’t know before. We enjoyed a lovely experience there with delicious cooking and a professional team and a great chief cook. We put this venue in our list  and we shall certainly come back very soon. We warmly recommend.
Best
Asian food... excellent. i've had nothing but pleasant experiences here and plan to keep coming back. this place has a great atmosphere. menu is like a cafe in indianapolis i loved.

Go... The spicy pork burrito is one of the best pandemic meals I've had.  Cheesy kimchi rice balls are interesting and worth trying...  Tiny counter service space, but absolutely worth seeking out.   I could come back every day for weeks.
Would definitely recommend visiting this place. Exceptional mood, flavorful dishes, good service. I recommend this place.

We decided to get delivery from OliToki, and it was really good! We ordered the Toki Totchos, Cheesy Kimchi Fried Rice Balls, and OliToki Burrito. Totchos were fantastic. Easily the best thing we ordered. Rice Balls we're good but not as flavorful as the Totchos. The Burritos (we ordered bulgogi and spicy pork) depend on if you like kimchi. It kind of overpowers everything else. All in all though, this was really good and reasonably priced.
My favorite restaurant in boston!
The customer service is regularly fast, excellent atmosphere, very nice employees. I will eat here again when I arrive in town.

The food is fine but the portions are just too small. The average American weighs 27% heavier than a South Korean, and the proprietors need to take that into account. Please adjust your recipes accordingly.

This site is my favorite site.  Of all restaurants I know I prefere it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to that place. Whenever  I want to go to a delicious meal, this place comes first to my mind. excellent and many types of  food and a rich menu.courteous team, and great vibes. Also important, the tariff is reasonable. I sent my friends to this place with pleasure.
The customer service is constantly prompt, excellent vibes, kind staff. I will visit here again when I arrive in town.

Definitely a hidden gem. It's very small and you could easily miss it on the street. Most of the menu can be customized to your liking. I recommend the Dumpling Munchies Bowl with soy garlic chicken and Spam Musube. The ramen seasoned fries are great option to share and they have some hard to find Korean and Japanese drinks.

We met with friends at this restaurant for a meeting. This place was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, it was a winning. The crew were very polite and we felt excellent. The food was just great. We loved this place very much and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Keep it up.
Had a good experience in this place with my kids. The food arrived quick and the customer service is just great. Prices are affordable.
Best Korean tacos I've ever had.

This place is clearly one of the coolest place to eat in the region. Always when I go there I am highly pleased. They hold their very high  level service and the highest level of meals  they give. You will be always satisfied with this place. Warmly  recommended.
Love the food! Better to take out than to dine in

I MUST SAY THIS IS MY FAVORITE FUSION IN BOSTON! Just try the beef bulgogi packed bowl extra spicy with added avocado and kimchi rice!!!! It’s heavenly delicious!!!! Also their olitoki wings wins! YUM YUM!!!! Can’t get enough!
This spot simply knows how to treat their customers. Consistently with a very kind demeanor. The food is conveniently priced, regularly yummy and neat.

Luckily my friend made reservations, strongly recommended because it seemed pretty crowded even around 9pm.  Very casual place with exceptional food.  As part of their specials, they had the scallops and they were absolutely one of the best I've ever tasted! Nothing else mattered, but I want everyone know to get the scallops if they're available!!!! PLEASE.
Small counterspace with a few tables, more suited to takeout. Quick service. Very interesting combinations of flavors. Try the rice balls, they're always delicious if they're on the menu.
Good Korean food

Great location, friendly staff, creative snack options with a fusion of the best Korean and Mexican flavors. Seemed like most customers were people that worked in the food delivery service. I ordered the Toki Totchos (a play on tater tots and nachos with kimchi salsa and spicy aioli). Highlights were the crispness of the tots and prudent mix of spices. Lows were the amount of oil that the added sweet and spicy pork and the craving for better cheese. Overall, I enjoyed what I ordered. Last note: given the portion size and calories, their food is definitely meant to be shared unless you want to be one really comatose person.
I had the beef burrito and very much liked the sauce they had on it.
Very unique fusion food that is both delicious and cheap.

Honestly I'm not sure about the hype of this place. The Mexican-Korean fusion isn't executed all that well. The novelty of you saying "wow, I'm eating a kimchi burrito" wears off quickly after you taste it

Definitely go with friends so you can order a lot and share. Great prices, speedy service, outstanding value. When you need a little variety in your tacos, Korean fusion is the way to go. I wasn't quite sure how it would turn out the first time I ate there and my fears disappeared immediately. I usually go for the tacos with chicken, but the seasoned pork and bulgogi beef are worth having. The burritos are out of this world with bacon fried rice & kimchi, and both the totchos and ramen-seasoned fries are a must-try. (Ignore the ketchup packets with the fries.) And the kimchi rice balls are perfect for fans of arancini.
Had no idea Korean-Mexican fusion was what was missing in my life. The beef burrito is bomb.
Definitely interesting, but not particularly savory meals if you're itching for Korean food. Good if you're looking for something out of the ordinary.
Better than I thought it would be. Small place for some Korean fast food.

It was good just not great for me. I love Korean food so maybe I had high expectations. We had the taco with bulgogi and the meat didn't have a ton of flavor, the tortilla was a bit too hard. The rice ball was good. It's ok for a quick lunch I just didn't like it enough to come back.

I popped by here for lunch yesterday and had a great, protein and flavor packed rice bowl! I went on the later side of lunch so the place was empty which was great because I was hangry. The space itself isn’t anything to write home about—it’s really more of a take-out joint. I had been meaning to swing by for a while, so I had a lot of questions for the staff member working about what I should try as a first-timer. Luckily for me as a pescatarian, he said that the kimchi rice balls didn’t have any meat in them! Win! They’re a cheesy, crispy, kimchi-filled delight. All of his recommendations were on point—the crispy tofu was super crunchy, the spicy toki sauce added great flavor, and the avocado he added on top helped temper the heat. At $9 for a huge rice bowl it’s really a lunch no-brainer. It’d be nice if they could make the space feel more homey and suited to people that want to sit and stay for a while. In any case, I’ll definitely be back for more food.
Service was slow and I did not receive the food that I ordered. The food that I did end up receiving was pretty good, though.

Fast and tasty food with friendly staff! This place is exactly what I was expecting. Mexican style food with Korean flavors. My table ordered the bulgogi tacos, kimchi burilla, and loaded tots. A waitress brought everything out on a tray. My favorite were the tacos although the meat wasn’t as hot as I would have liked. I’d definitely order again. The rest of the food was pretty tasty! One thing to note is they use the same seasonings in most of the food so it can start to blend together if you’ve ordered multiple things... butt totally okay with me for a street food fix.
The kimchi dumpling rice bowl is one of my favorite takeout dishes in the city.
Best find in Boston!! Friendly staff and the food is amazing!! Would definitely recommend!

Great little hole in the wall. Varied selection of tasty fusion Korean dishes. Portions are decent, not generous but you won't feel ripped off.  The restaurant itself is very small and clearly is geared toward takeout or delivery. The heating inside was very poor so we had to keep our jackets on for the whole meal.  Would recommend ordering ahead as the food is prepped fresh and therefore takes awhile.
(Translated by Google) The best place to eat the best fusion, Mexican cuisine and Korean cuisine!  (Original) El mejor lugar para comer la mejor fusión, cocina mexicana y cocina coreana!
Good food. Fast service
Great for bowls and fusion food.

Love this place. I’ve only ever ordered takeout or delivery, so I can’t really speak to the restaurant space, but the food never lets me down. Always recommending it to my friends and coworkers. Kimchi burrito might be my favorite thing ever.
Amazing food and friendly service.
Kimchi burrila is the best
Always excellent food, very friendly owner. Love olitoki and highly recommend it!
the food was delicious but the chicken was little dry.  The spicy level was really good though!
I had a kimchi bowl and I regret it since it was tasteless and the place was horrible. There wasn’t much sauce on it and kimchi dumpling was honestly one of the worst in my life
Super delicious food at super reasonable prices and the staff is super friendly!

Good food, good staff. It’s kind of a takeout place. Definitely try the rice balls. They have good fried tofu. They do have place to sit but it’s not that good. I would rather suggest to do a takeout. Boneless chicken was good too, try it with the in-house special sauce.
Their kimche tacos are amazing!

I have ordered their food many times thru Foodler and then thru Grubhub when Foodler got bought. Tonight was my first time in the little shop. There’s a really cool blackboard to look at while you wait and they play good music. The TV was showing a very interesting cooking show. Nice place to chill, great food, great people! I highly recommend the spam musubi!!!
Great service. The wings and ramen fries are definitely worth a try. Looking forward to trying more from their menu.
Korean fusion done right. Simple menu. Unique and flavorful. If you're worried one ingredient, don't. It all blends together we'll.
Food was fantastic

Undeniably cool/cute aesthetic. Really tastey fusion food that brings unique flavors. At the very least worth a try. It seems like most people order for delivery rather than eat at the location. Not that there's anything wrong with the location, it's just little
order for delivery and enjoy your meal 2 hours later

This is comfort food at its best. I highly recommend the to those loaded up with bacon kimchi fried rice. The ramen fries are also awesome. Just make sure you've got a drink cause it's all super salty and good!
Very slow
This fusion is the only type ever needed. Asian and Mexican the best of both worlds
Inexpensive and yummy Korean fusion food. Very casual eating space and smallish menu.
Omg the Tofu Burrito is amazing.
Enjoy the food. Trying new things. Korean & Mexican fusion

Great people. Great food. Everything is delicious here.
This place is the best!!! They're the nicest people and have great food and great service.
Great food, great service... And they deliver!
The food came was okay. Nothing too impressive.
Wings are good, and so are the fries. Everything else isn't.
Tacos were decent. Food was alright overall. I thought there'd be more options and the Korean aspect was gimmicky and felt disingenuous.

This spot has fun and funky vibe paired with friendly service.  I didn't feel pressured or rushed, and my food came out super quick.  My hubby and I got so distracted with how yummy our food was and we devoured it before I remembered to take pictures.  We got way more food than we expected for the price, and I'll most likely be happily waddling around after this.  I'll definitely be back.  Also, bunnies.
I had the bowl with bulgogi and it wasn't good. There are better options in the area, the offering had little meat and flavor. The sauce was okay, nothing special

This place is amazing. I ate here like 5 times in the last month. The boneless wings are amazing with the OliToki sauce. The Taco's are great. The burrito's wicked good. I HATE kimchi but the Kimchi Fried Rice Balls with bacon are sinfully good. Also with direct competition from other Korean-X fusion places in a five minute walking distance they lead the pack!  Also, if your are feeling as if you want to try a Filipino style side, try the Spam Matsubi.  The only thing that didn't blow me away was the bowl, but I may have been expecting something different in my mind.

Really good korean fried chicken wings. Tacos were tasty as well.
Great place for a korean fusion food, but the restaurant is super small. And it's probably better to do take out.
pretty good kimchi burrito
Amazing.
I cannot get enough of their totchos!! They are unreal. I dream about them!
This place has amazing food! Their loaded tacos are phenomenal. And don't even get me started with their bacon kimchi fried rice balls...they are absolutely soul-melting, a must try!

Super yummy Korean fusion food. I've tried almost everything on the menu and nothing has disappointed. The bacon kimchi fried rice balls are my favorite so far. The "Chorta" (torta) is delicious and filling. I can finally get some Korean tacos in my hood.
